  "description": "This model, first of all, is distinguished by a stylish case design with an external touch control panel, which looks as organic as possible against the background of the refrigerator door. However, the internal equipment of the model is not inferior to its design and also deserves the closest attention. At the heart of the device is a reliable, energy-efficient and quiet inverter compressor, and each of the chambers received a separate cooling circuit, which allows them to be completely independently regulated. The cooling system provides support for dynamic cooling technology and DoorCooling + technology, which ensures uniform and fast cooling of all shelves and baskets, including door ones. According to the manufacturer, the cooling rate is 32% faster than models without this technology. The total useful volume of the LG GB-B92MCACP refrigerator is 384 liters, of which 277 liters are in the refrigerator compartment, and 107 liters in the freezer. The equipment of the refrigerator compartment includes special FRESHBalancer humidity and FRESHConverter freshness zones, as well as a shelf for bottles. Freezer capacity reaches 10 kg/day. Thanks to Full No Frost technology, there is no need to periodically defrost the chamber to clear frost. The level of noise generated during operation does not exceed 35 dB, which allows us to rank the model among the quietest refrigerators on the market at the time the device was released.",
